{"data": {"blog": {"protocol-work-group-call-#8-3272": {"": "**Moderator:** @victorkanu1.near\\\\n \\\\n#### Summary\\\\n \\\\nThe NEAR Protocol Work Group voted on NEP-519 (Support for yielded execution.)\\\\n\\\\nWith all voting indications leaning towards approval, NEP-519 was approved by the Work Group, This proposal introduces the capability for smart contracts in the NEAR protocol to delay responding to callers until observing future transactions, addressing situations where immediate responses are not feasible.\\\\n\\\\nA big thank you was extended to the author for submitting this NEP and to everyone who helped review them. \\\\nThe recording will be posted on our YouTube https://youtube.com/@NEARDevHub/videos\\\\n \\\\n**Recording**: Learn more about NEP-519 [here](https://t.co/4R828Ho4p0)", "metadata": {"id": "3272", "title": "Protocol Work Group Call #8", "author": "victorkanu1.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "news", "subtitle": "Voting on NEP-519", "createdAt": "2024-04-30", "updatedAt": "2024-04-30", "description": "Voting on NEP-519", "publishedAt": "2024-04-30", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "protocol"}

{"data": {"protocol.community.devhub.near": {"blog": {"protocol-work-group-call-#8-3272": {"": "**Moderator:** @victorkanu1.near\\\\n \\\\n#### Summary\\\\n \\\\nThe NEAR Protocol Work Group voted on NEP-519 (Support for yielded execution.)\\\\n\\\\nWith all voting indications leaning towards approval, NEP-519 was approved by the Work Group, This proposal introduces the capability for smart contracts in the NEAR protocol to delay responding to callers until observing future transactions, addressing situations where immediate responses are not feasible.\\\\n\\\\nA big thank you was extended to the author for submitting this NEP and to everyone who helped review them. \\\\nThe recording will be posted on our YouTube https://youtube.com/@NEARDevHub/videos\\\\n \\\\n**Recording**: Learn more about NEP-519 [here](https://t.co/4R828Ho4p0)", "metadata": {"id": "3272", "title": "Protocol Work Group Call #8", "author": "victorkanu1.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "news", "subtitle": "Voting on NEP-519", "createdAt": "2024-04-30", "updatedAt": "2024-04-30", "description": "Voting on NEP-519", "publishedAt": "2024-04-30", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}}}

{"data": {"blog": {"[community-call]---may-25th,-2023-3273": {"": "\\\\nAnyone can propose topics and join the community call for discussion.\\\\n\\\\n**MODERATOR:** Maxwell S\\\\n\\\\n**VIDEO:** [Contract Standards Community Group Call #3 \\\\u{2013} NEAR DevHub September 27th, 2023\\\\n](https://youtu.be/T0qMj1zGA3U)\\\\n\\\\n**AGENDA** \\\\n- Discussion on incentivizing completion of the Multitoken standard and what the blockers might be.\\\\n\\\\n**OUTCOMES**\\\\n- Ken from NEAR Horizon offered to do some unblocking work to move NEP-245 forward in the coming weeks.\\\\n\\\\n \\\\n", "metadata": {"id": "undefined", "title": "[Community Call] - May 25th, 2023", "author": "victorkanu1.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "news", "subtitle": "", "createdAt": "2024-04-07", "updatedAt": "2024-04-07", "description": "", "publishedAt": "2024-04-07", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "contract-standards"}

{"data": {"blog": {"[working-group-call]---june-30th,-2023--3274": {"": "\\\\n**MODERATOR :** Maxwell S\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**VIDEO :** [Contract Standards Work Group Meeting \\\\u{2013} June 30th, 2023](https://youtu.be/S1An5CDG154)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**AGENDA**\\\\n\\\\n* Objective\\\\n* Introductions\\\\n* Discussion: NEP-393 Soulbound Token\\\\n* Voting Decision\\\\n* Getting Involved\\\\n* NOTES\\\\n\\\\n**NEP-393 Soulbound Token**: This NEP introduces wallet-bound non-fungible tokens on NEAR, known as Soulbound tokens. These tokens cannot be easily transferred from wallet to wallet, serving as a form of wallet identification and credentialing. This implementation includes tools for transferring credentials, such as bans or deletions, of the transferring wallet.\\\\nVOTE DECISION\\\\n\\\\n**NEP-393: Approved**\\\\n\\\\n**ACTION ITEMS**\\\\n- Robert Z: Fill out the \\\\\\\"Changelog\\\\\\\" section in the NEP with the reference to the video recording of WG call, benefit and concerns table.\\\\n- Vlad F: Approve and merge the NEP.\\\\n- Robert Z: Endorse SBT support in Wallets.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**RELATED RESOURCES**\\\\n\\\\n- NEP-393 Soulbound Token on GitHub: [LINK](https://github.com/near/NEPs/pull/393)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n ", "metadata": {"id": "undefined", "title": "[Working Group Call] - June 30th, 2023 ", "author": "victorkanu1.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "news", "subtitle": "", "createdAt": "2024-04-07", "updatedAt": "2024-04-07", "description": "", "publishedAt": "2024-04-07", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "contract-standards"}

{"data": {"contract-standards.community.devhub.near": {"blog": {"[working-group-call]---june-30th,-2023--3274": {"": "\\\\n**MODERATOR :** Maxwell S\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**VIDEO :** [Contract Standards Work Group Meeting \\\\u{2013} June 30th, 2023](https://youtu.be/S1An5CDG154)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**AGENDA**\\\\n\\\\n* Objective\\\\n* Introductions\\\\n* Discussion: NEP-393 Soulbound Token\\\\n* Voting Decision\\\\n* Getting Involved\\\\n* NOTES\\\\n\\\\n**NEP-393 Soulbound Token**: This NEP introduces wallet-bound non-fungible tokens on NEAR, known as Soulbound tokens. These tokens cannot be easily transferred from wallet to wallet, serving as a form of wallet identification and credentialing. This implementation includes tools for transferring credentials, such as bans or deletions, of the transferring wallet.\\\\nVOTE DECISION\\\\n\\\\n**NEP-393: Approved**\\\\n\\\\n**ACTION ITEMS**\\\\n- Robert Z: Fill out the \\\\\\\"Changelog\\\\\\\" section in the NEP with the reference to the video recording of WG call, benefit and concerns table.\\\\n- Vlad F: Approve and merge the NEP.\\\\n- Robert Z: Endorse SBT support in Wallets.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**RELATED RESOURCES**\\\\n\\\\n- NEP-393 Soulbound Token on GitHub: [LINK](https://github.com/near/NEPs/pull/393)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n ", "metadata": {"id": "undefined", "title": "[Working Group Call] - June 30th, 2023 ", "author": "victorkanu1.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "news", "subtitle": "", "createdAt": "2024-04-07", "updatedAt": "2024-04-07", "description": "", "publishedAt": "2024-04-07", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}}}

{"data": {"blog": {"documentation-community-call-#8-3281": {"": "**Updates from Moderator**\\\\n\\\\n1. Completed migration of documentation files to improve consistency and organization, addressing issues with URLs, internal links, and translations.\\\\n2. Implemented improvements to address issues with the documentation structure, internal linking, and translations, requiring significant effort due to the need for manual adjustments and scripting.\\\\n3. Working on establishing a blog within the documentation to provide additional context, explanations, and announcements, enhancing the user experience.\\\\n4. Conducted analysis on frontend development practices, focusing on React vs. vanilla JavaScript, to streamline the process and align with community preferences.\\\\n5. Upcoming focus on migrating the Nifty tutorial, addressing technical challenges and ensuring compatibility with SDK 5.0.\\\\n6. Plans to continue migrating examples to near-examples repository for better organization and accessibility, encouraging contributions and collaboration.\\\\n\\\\n**Summary of the Call:**\\\\n\\\\nThe community met for the 8th time to discuss updates and improvements to the documentation and developer resources. Guillermo provided insights into recent changes, including the migration of files, implementation of a blog, and analysis of frontend development practices. Discussions also touched on upcoming tasks, such as tutorial migrations and example consolidation. Overall, the goal is to enhance the user experience, streamline development processes, and foster collaboration within the community.\\\\n\\\\n**Recording:** [here](https://youtu.be/udCR59Bu2FI)", "metadata": {"id": "3281", "title": "Documentation Community Call #8", "author": "victorkanu1.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "guide", "subtitle": "", "createdAt": "2024-04-25", "updatedAt": "2024-04-25", "description": "", "publishedAt": "2024-04-25", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "documentation"}

{"data": {"blog": {"documentation-community-call-#9-3282": {"": "In the latest Docs community call, exciting updates and collaborations were shared, marking significant progress in documentation and tool development within the ecosystem.\\\\n\\\\n1. **Introduction of Code Explainer Tool:** Guillermo introduced a new tool aimed at enhancing code understanding, featuring a hide button for improved user experience and highlighting code snippets relevant to concepts discussed.\\\\n\\\\n2. **Enhancements to Create Near App:** Users can now opt for on-chain components when creating web applications, streamlining the development process and addressing user feedback.\\\\n\\\\n3. **Zero to Hero Tutorial Migration:** The NFT Zero to Hero tutorial has been fully migrated, thanks to the dedicated efforts of contributors, streamlining the learning journey for developers.\\\\n\\\\n4. **Consolidation of SDK Pages:** Efforts are underway to consolidate Near SDK pages to reduce redundancy and streamline searchability, ensuring developers find relevant information efficiently.\\\\n\\\\n5. **Future Developments:** Plans for multi-chain support, documentation improvements, and the development of an AI-driven assistant for navigating Docs were discussed, promising further enhancements to the ecosystem.\\\\n\\\\nThe community call concluded with anticipation for upcoming presentations on the dev.near.org plan, indicating a forward-looking approach to ecosystem growth and developer support.\\\\n\\\\n##### Watch the recording [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jt1JWWttCcs)", "metadata": {"id": "3282", "title": "Documentation Community Call #9", "author": "victorkanu1.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "guide", "subtitle": "", "createdAt": "2024-05-17", "updatedAt": "2024-05-17", "description": "", "publishedAt": "2024-05-17", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "documentation"}
